BT /F2 11 Tf 54 652.4 Td (THE 5 WAYS REAL ESTATE MAKES YOU MONEY:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 626.6 Td (1. CASH FLOW - Monthly rent minus expenses = money in your pocket) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 612.6 Td (   Example: $1,500 rent - $1,100 expenses = $400/month passive income) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 588.8 Td (2. APPRECIATION - Properties increase in value over time) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 574.8 Td (   Average: 3-5% per year. A $200K property = $210K in 2 years) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 551.0 Td (3. LEVERAGE - Use the bank's money to buy assets) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 537.0 Td (   Put $40K down on a $200K property = control $200K with $40K) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 513.2 Td (4. TAX BENEFITS - Depreciation, write-offs, 1031 exchanges) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 499.2 Td (   Real estate investors pay LESS tax than W-2 employees) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 475.4 Td (5. EQUITY BUILD-UP - Tenants pay down YOUR mortgage) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 461.4 Td (   Every month, you own more of the property. They pay, you benefit.) Tj ET
