BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (CHAPTER 2: TYPES OF REAL ESTATE INVESTMENTS) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 676.2 Td (1. SINGLE-FAMILY RENTALS \(Best for Beginners\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 660.2 Td (What: Buy a house, rent it out) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 646.2 Td (Pros: Easiest to finance, easiest to manage, easiest to sell) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 632.2 Td (Cons: One vacancy = 100% income loss) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 618.2 Td (Best for: First-time investors with $20-50K to start) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 590.4 Td (2. MULTI-FAMILY \(Duplex, Triplex, Fourplex\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 574.4 Td (What: 2-4 units in one building) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 560.4 Td (Pros: Multiple income streams, can house-hack \(live in one unit\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 546.4 Td (Cons: Slightly more management, higher purchase price) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 532.4 Td (Best for: House-hackers who want to live for free) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 504.6 Td (3. HOUSE HACKING \(Live Free Strategy\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 488.6 Td (What: Buy multi-unit, live in one, rent others) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 474.6 Td (Pros: FHA loan \(3.5% down\), tenants pay YOUR mortgage) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 460.6 Td (Cons: You live next to tenants) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 446.6 Td (Example: Buy duplex for $300K, rent one side for $1,500) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 432.6 Td (         Your mortgage: $2,000 - Rent: $1,500 = You pay only $500/month!) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 404.8 Td (4. FIX & FLIP) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 388.8 Td (What: Buy cheap, renovate, sell for profit) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 374.8 Td (Pros: Large lump-sum profits \($30-100K per flip\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 360.8 Td (Cons: Active work, renovation risk, capital intensive) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 346.8 Td (Best for: People with construction knowledge or contractor relationships) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 319.0 Td (5. SHORT-TERM RENTALS \(Airbnb\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 303.0 Td (What: Rent by the night/week on Airbnb/VRBO) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 289.0 Td (Pros: 2-3x higher income than long-term rental) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 275.0 Td (Cons: More management, seasonal, regulation risk) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 261.0 Td (Best for: Properties in tourist/business travel areas) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 233.2 Td (6. REAL ESTATE WHOLESALING \(No Money Needed\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 217.2 Td (What: Find deals, put under contract, sell the contract to investors) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 203.2 Td (Pros: Zero money needed, quick profits \($5-20K per deal\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 189.2 Td (Cons: Requires marketing/hustle, not truly passive) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 175.2 Td (Best for: Beginners with no capital but strong work ethic) Tj ET
endstream
