BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (CHAPTER 4: FINDING PROFITABLE DEALS) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 676.2 Td (THE 1% RULE \(Quick Screening Test\):) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 660.2 Td (Monthly rent should be at least 1% of purchase price) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 646.2 Td (Example: $200,000 property should rent for $2,000+/month) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 632.2 Td (If it passes 1% rule -> do deeper analysis) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 618.2 Td (If it fails -> move on \(most properties fail this test\)) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 590.4 Td (THE 70% RULE \(For Flips\):) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 574.4 Td (Max offer = \(ARV x 70%\) - Repair costs) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 560.4 Td (ARV = After Repair Value \(what it's worth fixed up\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 546.4 Td (Example: ARV $300K x 70% = $210K - $40K repairs = Max offer $170K) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 518.6 Td (WHERE TO FIND DEALS:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 502.6 Td (1. MLS \(Zillow, Redfin, Realtor.com\) - easiest but most competition) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 488.6 Td (2. Driving for Dollars - look for distressed properties) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 474.6 Td (3. Direct Mail to absentee owners / pre-foreclosures) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 460.6 Td (4. Wholesalers - they find deals and sell to you) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 446.6 Td (5. Auctions \(foreclosure, tax lien, estate\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 432.6 Td (6. FSBO \(For Sale By Owner\) - less competition) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 418.6 Td (7. Networking \(REI meetups, BiggerPockets forums\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 404.6 Td (8. Off-market: divorce attorneys, probate, estate sales) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 376.8 Td (RED FLAGS TO AVOID:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 360.8 Td ([ ] Foundation issues \(cracks, uneven floors\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 346.8 Td ([ ] Flood zones \(insurance kills cash flow\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 332.8 Td ([ ] War zones \(high crime = bad tenants + damage\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 318.8 Td ([ ] Properties that only work with 'optimistic' numbers) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 304.8 Td ([ ] Anything that fails the 1% rule significantly) Tj ET
endstream
